[postmark: Jan. 9, 1954]
Nelson Algen
6228 Forest Av.
Gary, Ind.
Completed

Dear Nelson,
Blake is in again. This time he faces 5 to 10. I'm really on a bum kick and brought way down because of it. Despite the jokes I didn't believe he would go back. That must be that naivete I read about. His address is 3-W Pinellas County Jail, Clearwater, Fla. The envelope had a return c/o Sid Sanders Hotel Clearwater, Fla.
He seems happy about it, although that's probably bravado or  unclear.
Yrs,
B.
Completed

1-19-54
Dear Bud

  Thanks for the program glad you landed job  Enclose Withholding statement and notice of Insurance I do not think much of this company.

Mom and Aunt Celia have gone to Doctor  Im going to Tavern
Love Papa Joe
Completed

Went down swingin on the last day, Dad, trying to get even.
    Should have saved it for Myrtle, Arlington and Blankenship.
   With only one yoke I'm lost.  What will I do with all that extry time?

A degenerate horse player.

[postcard]
Dear Jack -

 Blake is putting a story his current wife and/or husband has written, to music  Look out there Liberace here I come.  It is a western.
 You should see the expression on the face of the cat who offers a New Testament free to those who will read it.   He's stationed in front of a Kosher rest on Miami Beach.

Yrs,
B
